{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":36199,"record_hash":"sha256:31a839370c0604486a429b1d8981eb6de4b55ea0716e40f2a6b2d4ac96680417","timestamp":"2026-05-12T08:36:53.446Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: 7f7bbf\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 1462\nOutput:\n# GitMeta Data Model\n\n## Principles\n\n- Store durable agent sessions on the `project` target.\n- Use shareable-ready `gitbutler:*` keys for GitButler agentlog data.\n- Do not use `meta:local:*` for main session records.\n- Redact copied transcript strings before writing.\n- Keep branch, pull request, change, and commit links as references to durable\n  project sessions, not owners of transcript data.\n- Do not write standard `agent:*` keys until there is an interoperability or\n  publication contract.\n- Capture does not call GitMeta serialize, push, fetch, or sync. Hook capture\n  schedules the existing sync command in the background after successful\n  capture.\n- Do not persist capture-run buckets. Each invocation merges transcript records\n  into the same durable session data.\n\n## Storage Shape\n\nSession index:\n\n```text\ngitbutler:agent-sessions = set<session-key>\n```\n\nDurable session prefix:\n\n```text\ngitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:*\n```\n\nSession-level keys:\n\n```text\ngitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:schema = gitbutler.agent-session.v1\ngitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:updated-at = <session update timestamp>\ngitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:sources = set<source-key>\ngitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:record-hashes = set<sha256:record>\ngitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:transcript = list<TranscriptRecord JSON>\n```\n\nSource-level keys:\n\n```text\ngitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:source:<source-key>:agent\ngitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:source:<source-key>:provider\ngitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:source:<source-key>:model\ngitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:source:<source-key>:tool-version\n```\n\nDo not store full transcript paths, source file names, git branch names, or raw\nprovider session ids as session/source metadata.\n\n## Session And Source Keys\n\nProvider session ids are opaque and may contain private identifiers. Do not put\nthe raw provider session id in GitMeta keys or s\n[TRUNCATED]\nments/input copied into `tool_input`, and tool\nresult output copied into `text` are removed from `source_record`. Large\n`tool_result` text is capped at 4 KiB so one command cannot dominate the session\nrecord. Mixed provider content is kept when removing copied text would also drop\nuncopied sibling data.\n\nOmit repeated session/source metadata from each transcript record. Also omit git\nbranch, provider session ids, message ids, parent ids, and turn ids from\ntop-level record fields.\n\nRecord hashes and dedupe use the original trimmed JSONL bytes, not the redacted\ntranscript record.\n\nStored GitMeta list order is not the public transcript ordering contract.\nConsumers that render a timeline should sort by transcript fields. Within one\nsource, sort by `source_key` and `record_index`; across multiple sources, use\n`timestamp`, `source_key`, `record_index`, and `record_hash` as stable tie\nbreakers.\n\n## Deduplication\n\nUse stable record hashes:\n\n```text\nsha256(trimmed raw JSONL line bytes)\n```\n\nCapture checks `:record-hashes` before appending transcript records. The\ntranscript list remains the append-friendly storage value; the hash set is the\ncompact dedupe index. Re-running capture against the same transcript is a no-op\nunless the transcript grew.\n\n## Association Model\n\nDo not attach transcript data directly to branches, commits, changes, or pull\nrequests in the POC. The project session is the durable object.\n\nWhen capture is given an explicit association target, write only this\nrelationship reference:\n\n```text\n<branch/change/commit target>\n  gitbutler:agent-sessions = set<session-key>\n```\n\nSee [Future Use Cases](future-use-cases.md) for access patterns and product\nmotivation.\n\n## Publication\n\nThe POC writes shareable-ready keys. `but agentlog sync` is the exchange step\nand uses GitMeta's configured metadata remote behavior. Hook capture starts that\nsame command in the background after a successful capture. Sync is not scoped to\nthe `gitbutler:*` agentlog keys, so it may exchange other shareable GitMeta\nmetadata too.\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-12T08:36:53.446Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}